Data prepare

sce <- readRDS("../02_raw_data/E-MTAB-8322.rds")
met <- read_xlsx("../03_meta_data/E.MTAB.8322.simplified.xlsx")
met <- met[c(1:4,9:10,15:17,22:23,25:26,7,8,5,6,14,11,12,13,18,19,20,21,24,27),]
met$sample_id[14:27] <- c("NaiveSA131", "NaiveSA138","NaiveSA146", "NaiveSA172", "RemSA132", "RemSA160" ,
                         "RemSA161", "RemSA174", "ResistantSA144", "ResistantSA145", "ResistantSA151",
                          "ResistantSA166", "UPASA149", "UPASA153")
met$cohort <- "discovery"
met$cohort[5:13] <- "validation"
colnames(met)[1] <- "orig.ident"
id <- data.frame(sce$orig.ident)
colnames(id) <- "orig.ident"
met1 <- left_join(id,met,"orig.ident")
rownames(met1) <- colnames(sce)
met1$row_names <- rownames(met1)
write_csv(met1, "sce_meta.csv")
sce <- AddMetaData(object = sce,metadata= met1)
#saveRDS(sce,"E-MTAB-8322_with_meta.RDS")
sce <- readRDS("../04_data_objects/E-MTAB-8322_with_meta.RDS")

Select cells for further analysis

  • We filter cells that more than three median absolute deviations (MADs) of the log10 read counts below the median.
  • We filter cells that more than three MADs of the log10 genes detected below the median.
  • We filter cells that more than more than three MADs of the genes coming from mitochondria above the median.
min.nfeatures.thr <- median(log10(pbmc$nFeature_RNA)) - 3*mad(log10(pbmc$nFeature_RNA))
max.nfeatures.thr <- median(log10(pbmc$nFeature_RNA)) + 3*mad(log10(pbmc$nFeature_RNA))

min.ncount.thr <- median(log10(pbmc$nCount_RNA)) - 3*mad(log10(pbmc$nCount_RNA))
max.ncount.thr <- median(log10(pbmc$nCount_RNA)) + 3*mad(log10(pbmc$nCount_RNA))

min.mito.thr <- median(pbmc$percent.mt) - 3*mad(pbmc$percent.mt)
max.mito.thr <- median(pbmc$percent.mt) + 3*mad(pbmc$percent.mt)

nfeatures.passed <- log10(pbmc$nFeature_RNA) > min.nfeatures.thr & 
  log10(pbmc$nFeature_RNA) < max.nfeatures.thr
ncount.passed <- log10(pbmc$nCount_RNA) > min.ncount.thr & 
  log10(pbmc$nCount_RNA) < max.ncount.thr
mito.passed <- pbmc$percent.mt > min.mito.thr &
  pbmc$percent.mt < max.mito.thr

pbmc.sel <- pbmc[,which(nfeatures.passed & ncount.passed & mito.passed)]
#saveRDS(pbmc.sel, file = "SeuratObject_27subjects_ncounts_nfeatures_mito_3MAD.RDS")
## nFeature_RNA
qc.p1 <- VlnPlot(pbmc.sel, 
        features = "nFeature_RNA", 
        ncol = 3,
        pt.size = 0,
        group.by = "orig.ident",
        raster=FALSE) +
 # scale_fill_prism(palette = "floral") +
  theme(legend.position="none",
        axis.title.x = element_blank())

qc.p2 <- VlnPlot(pbmc.sel, 
        features = "nFeature_RNA", 
        ncol = 3,
        pt.size = 0,
        group.by = "group_id") +
 # scale_fill_prism(palette = "prism_dark") +
  theme(legend.position="none",
        axis.title.x = element_blank())

grid.arrange(qc.p1, qc.p2, ncol = 2)
